  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhance Management in IDPs Sites and Provide Emergency Shelter and NFI Assistance to Conflict-Affected Populations in Middle Belt Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM aims to implement activities in displacement management system (DMS) and Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM), and it intends to address the gaps identified by the inter-agency rapid assessment mission on humanitarian needs led by OCHA in February 2018 in Logo, Guma and Makurdi Local Government Authority (LGAs) in Benue State and Awe LGA in Nasarawa State through: Coordination of camp activities and active sectors at eight IDP camps or camp-like settings; Improving site management by further strengthening site management structures and enabling stronger leadership; Enhancing knowledge of site management and mobilization of community committees for National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) and other local stakeholders; as well as provide direct assistance to households in the same locations, through Emergency Shelter kits and Non-Food Item (NFI) kits.</narrative>
  </description>
